article.headline: N.C.-Asheville 83, Campbell 71
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Reserve Kenny George turned in a triple-double with 20 points, 12 rebounds and 10 blocked shots as unbeaten North Carolina-Asheville beat Campbell 83-71 Saturday. The 7-foot-7 George hit all eight shots he tried for the Bulldogs (4-0). His blocks tied his school and Big South Conference record, and helped the Bulldogs set a school and conference mark with 16 blocks in the non-conference game. Brandon Davis drew UNC-Asheville to 19-16 on a 3-pointer with 12:25 left in the first half. The Camels (1-2) responded with a 12-3 run capped by Reggie Bishop's layup with 8:44 left before the half. Campbell held a 41-34 lead at the break, but the Bulldogs rallied, and a dunk by George with 13:24 left to play tied the score at 47. The lead would change hands three times before a 3-point shot by K.J. Garland helped UNC-Asheville take a 55-53 edge with 9:48 to go. That shot sparked an 18-3 run that put the Bulldogs out of reach. Garland led UNC-Asheville with 23 points. Vincent James and John Williams scored 11 points apiece for the Bulldogs, who shot 55 percent in the second half. Kyle Vejraska scored 15 points for the Camels, whose shooting touch faltered to 24 percent in the second half. Jonathan Rodriguez had 13 points and 13 rebounds for Campbell.
